<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 07 at 12:29AM EDT  by NWS NorthernIndiana</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Cass, northwestern
St. Joseph and east central Berrien Counties through 130 AM EDT...
At 1229 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Marcellus to near Niles. Movement was
southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Marcellus around 1235 AM EDT.
Other locations in the path of these storms include Cassopolis and
Three Rivers.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
